<paragraph blockId="199.[151,1437,1705,1846]" pageId="199" pageNumber="200">
<emphasis box="[196,451,1745,1769]" italics="true" pageId="199" pageNumber="200">Diagnostic characters</emphasis>
: The male imago can be distinguished from 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Tokunaga" baseAuthorityYear="1964" box="[990,1131,1745,1769]" class="Insecta" family="Chironomidae" genus="Pseudosmittia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="199" pageNumber="200" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="triangula">
<emphasis box="[990,1007,1745,1768]" italics="true" pageId="199" pageNumber="200">P</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[1027,1131,1745,1769]" italics="true" pageId="199" pageNumber="200">triangula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by having a slight apical projection on the anal point, and AR of about 0.9, 8 dorsocentrals and a costal extension of 7 µm.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="199.[151,1437,1705,1846]" box="[196,1157,1822,1846]" pageId="199" pageNumber="200">
<emphasis box="[196,316,1822,1846]" italics="true" pageId="199" pageNumber="200">Etymology</emphasis>
: From 
<collectingCountry box="[398,458,1822,1846]" name="Thailand" pageId="199" pageNumber="200">Siam</collectingCountry>
, the old name for 
<collectingCountry box="[661,763,1822,1846]" name="Thailand" pageId="199" pageNumber="200">Thailand</collectingCountry>
, and the Latin - 
<emphasis box="[939,995,1823,1846]" italics="true" pageId="199" pageNumber="200">ensis</emphasis>
, belonging to.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="199.[151,1437,1891,2032]" box="[151,368,1891,1915]" pageId="199" pageNumber="200">
<emphasis box="[151,285,1891,1915]" italics="true" pageId="199" pageNumber="200">Male imago</emphasis>
(n = 1)
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="199.[151,1437,1891,2032]" lastBlockId="200.[151,1437,158,308]" lastPageId="200" lastPageNumber="201" pageId="199" pageNumber="200">
All measurements within the range of variation or less than 4 µm different from the range in 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Tokunaga" baseAuthorityYear="1964" box="[1189,1324,1930,1954]" class="Insecta" family="Chironomidae" genus="Pseudosmittia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="199" pageNumber="200" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="triangula">
<emphasis box="[1189,1206,1931,1954]" italics="true" pageId="199" pageNumber="200">P</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[1220,1324,1930,1954]" italics="true" pageId="199" pageNumber="200">triangula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, all ratios within 0.02 of the variation in 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Tokunaga" baseAuthorityYear="1964" box="[514,653,1969,1993]" class="Insecta" family="Chironomidae" genus="Pseudosmittia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="199" pageNumber="200" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="triangula">
<emphasis box="[514,531,1969,1992]" italics="true" pageId="199" pageNumber="200">P</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[549,653,1969,1993]" italics="true" pageId="199" pageNumber="200">triangula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, with the following exceptions or additions: Wing length/length of profemur 2.95. AR 0.91, terminal flagellomere 242 µm long, no strong apical seta. Dorsocentral setae 8, scutellum with 4 setae. Costal extension (
<figureCitation box="[506,618,158,182]" captionStart="FIGURE 75" captionStartId="200.[151,250,1762,1785]" captionTargetBox="[254,1323,589,1737]" captionTargetId="figure-176@200.[226,1361,566,1777]" captionTargetPageId="200" captionText="FIGURE 75. Pseudosmittia siamensis sp. n., male. A—wing; B—head; C—cibarial pump; D—virga; E—hypopygium." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5288525" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5288525/files/figure.png" pageId="200" pageNumber="201">Fig. 75 A</figureCitation>
) 7 µm long, with false vein extending 160 µm long, postcubitus forked. Front femur 252 µm long, ta 
<subScript attach="left" box="[468,476,212,226]" fontSize="6" pageId="200" pageNumber="201">1</subScript>
of front leg 162 µm long, ta 
<subScript attach="left" box="[790,798,212,226]" fontSize="6" pageId="200" pageNumber="201">2</subScript>
63 µm long, ta 
<subScript attach="left" box="[967,975,212,226]" fontSize="6" pageId="200" pageNumber="201">3</subScript>
45 µm long; ta 
<subScript attach="left" box="[1145,1153,212,226]" fontSize="6" pageId="200" pageNumber="201">1</subScript>
of hind leg 189 µm long. BV 
<subScript attach="left" box="[190,198,255,269]" fontSize="6" pageId="200" pageNumber="201">1</subScript>
4.05, BV 
<subScript attach="left" box="[310,318,255,269]" fontSize="6" pageId="200" pageNumber="201">2</subScript>
3.76, SV 
<subScript attach="left" box="[427,435,255,269]" fontSize="6" pageId="200" pageNumber="201">2</subScript>
3.33. Anal point (
<figureCitation box="[647,756,240,264]" captionStart="FIGURE 75" captionStartId="200.[151,250,1762,1785]" captionTargetBox="[254,1323,589,1737]" captionTargetId="figure-176@200.[226,1361,566,1777]" captionTargetPageId="200" captionText="FIGURE 75. Pseudosmittia siamensis sp. n., male. A—wing; B—head; C—cibarial pump; D—virga; E—hypopygium." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5288525" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5288525/files/figure.png" pageId="200" pageNumber="201">Fig. 75 E</figureCitation>
) triangular with apical projection; tergite IX including anal point with 16 setae; laterosternite IX with 2 setae. Gonostylus 51 µm long. HR 2.18, HV 2.66.
</paragraph>
